Sales Prediction using Python
1. Introduction

Sales prediction is one of the most important applications of Machine Learning in business analytics. It helps organizations estimate future sales based on historical advertising data. Accurate sales prediction enables companies to make better marketing decisions, allocate budgets efficiently, and maximize profits.

In this project, a Linear Regression model is developed to predict product sales using advertising expenditure on TV, Radio, and Newspaper. The project covers data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), visualization, model training, prediction, and performance evaluation.

2. Objective

The main objectives of this project are:

To analyze the advertising dataset.
To clean and preprocess the data.
To visualize the relationship between advertising expenditure and sales.
To build a Linear Regression model for predicting sales.
To evaluate the model using standard regression metrics.
To understand which advertising medium has the greatest impact on sales.
3. Dataset Description

The dataset used in this project is Advertising.csv.

It contains advertising budgets for different media platforms and the corresponding sales achieved.

Dataset Information
Dataset Name: Advertising.csv
Total Records: 200
Total Features (after cleaning): 4
Missing Values: 0
Duplicate Records: 0
Dataset Features
Feature	Description
TV	Advertising budget spent on TV (in thousands of dollars)
Radio	Advertising budget spent on Radio
Newspaper	Advertising budget spent on Newspaper
Sales	Product sales (Target Variable)
